Defendant Dominic Somk Panhyasiri in court with attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Defendant Dominic Somk Panhyasiri in custody.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.    The Court imposed the following sentence:   

The Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be two (2) years concurrent to 15CF1734.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for one (1) year with credit for 159 days time served.  Defendant shall serve one (1) year on EXTENDED SUPERVISION. The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of the determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant. 
 * DNA sample ordered in case 15CF1734.
 * Court ordered defendant to pay the DNA surcharge, plus costs and disbursements.  Court ordered monies to be taken by the Department of Corrections from up to 25% of prison funds.  Balance to be paid while on Extended Supervision.
 * No contact with Jb Hankins.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
 - No contact with Jane S., Amber W., Pick n' Save at 4145 North Oakland Avenue, Shorewood, Wisconsin; or George Webb at 3133 South 92nd Street, Milwaukee, Wisconsin;
 - Mental health evaluation and treatment; 
 - No controlled substances other than those legally prescribed for defendant by a duly licensed physician for his mental or physical needs; take as prescribed and only for as long as deemed medically reasonable and necessary.  
 - No alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Urine screens to ensure compliance;
 - Parenting classes;
 - Obtain HSED or GED;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - No contact with co-defendant Jb Hankins;
 - Court ordered defendant to pay any balances remaining of the costs, surcharges and disbursements.  Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

